To install dimRetEvoSim, download and unpack the tarball where you want
the installation (do e.g. "tar -xzf dimRetEvoSim_0.1.5.tar.gz"). 
Then run "make -s". If you want a different compiler or
mode than the defaults, then, instead of "make -s", use e.g.
"make gccrelease" or "make -s -f makefile_icc_release_static".

dimRetEvoSim uses getopt which isn't included in the dimRetEvoSim distribution.
If you don't have getopt, and don't want to install it, and
don't care about command line options in dimRetEvoSim, you can get by by
defining NoGetopt; you can do that by e.g. uncommenting the line
"#CFLAGS += -DNoGetopt" in makefile_core. You can still use 
dimRetEvoSim with default options.

